article.headline: Ohio 88, Bowling Green 63
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Whitney Davis had career highs of 26 points and nine rebounds to lead Ohio to a 88-63 victory over Bowling Green on Wednesday night. Leon Williams had 17 points and 15 rebounds, Bubba Walther added 13, Sonny Troutman 12 and Jerome Tillman 10 as all five starters hit double figures for the Bobcats (17-10, 8-5 Mid-American). Davis made 6 of 9 3-point shots and Ohio shot 44 percent (10-of-23) on 3s, while the Falcons shot 35 percent (7-of-20) from beyond the arc. The Bobcats outrebounded Bowling Green 44-27. Coming off an 11-point halftime lead, Ohio stretched it to 61-34 in the first six minutes of the second half. Troutman had three layups in the 19-3 stretch. Martin Samarco scored 19 points and Nate Miller had 16 points and nine rebounds for the Falcons (12-15, 2-11). The win snapped a three-game skid for the Bobcats.
